andhan: How effective is the alliance?|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/sp-bsp-gathbandhan-how-effective-is-the-alliance/videoshow/68852110.cms|access-date=2019-04-13|last2=2019|last3=Ist|first3=06 23 Pm}} {{verify source |date=August 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted ([[Special:Diff/895646183]]) by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite at [[Special:Permalink/895469470]] cite #12 - please verify the cite's accuracy and remove this {verify source} template. [[User:GreenC bot/Job 18]]}}</ref>\n\nThe ''Mahagathbandhan'' won 15 seats out of 80 in Uttar Pradesh in 2019 Indian General Election.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/elections/lok-sabha/uttar-pradesh/mahagathbandhan-in-up-losing-five-seats-because-of-congress-one-because-of-shivpal/articleshow/69461537.cms|title=Mahagathbandhan in UP losing five seats because of Congress, one because of Shivpal|last=Anshuman|first=Kumar|date=2019-05-23|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-05-29}}</ref>\n\n== Election results ==\n=== Lok Sabha (Lower House) ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#00f;\"\n! Lok Sabha Term\n! Indian<br />General Election\n! Seats<br />contested\n! Seats<br />won\n! % of<br /> votes\n! % of votes in<br />seats contested\n! State (seats)\n|-\n| [[9th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[1989 Indian general election|1989]]\n| 245\n| 4\n| 2.07\n| 4.53\n| Punjab (1)<br />Uttar Pradesh (3)<ref>{{cite web |title=Members : Lok Sabha |website=IIS Windows Server |date=2 May 2016 |url=http://164.100.47.192/Loksabha/members/partyardetail.aspx?party_code=26&lsno=9 |accessdate=2016-05-02}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[10th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[1991 Indian general election|1991]]\n| 231\n| 3\n| 1.61\n| 3.64\n| Madhya_Pradesh(1)<br />Punjab (1)<br />Uttar Pradesh (1)<ref>{{cite web |title=Members : Lok Sabha |website=IIS Windows Server |date=2 May 2016 |url=http://164.100.47.192/Loksabha/Members/lokaralpha.aspx?lsno=10&tab=5 |language=jv |accessdate=2016-05-02}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[11th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[1996 Indian general election|1996]]\n| 210\n| 11\n| 4.02\n| 11.21\n| Madhya Pradesh(2)<br />Punjab (3)<br />Uttar Pradesh (6)\n|-\n| [[12th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[1998 Indian general election|1998]]\n| 251\n| 5\n| 4.67\n| 9.84\n| Haryana (1)<br />Uttar Pradesh (4)\n|-\n| [[13th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[1999 Indian general election|1999]]\n| 225\n| 14\n| 4.16\n| 9.97\n| Uttar Pradesh (14)\n|-\n| [[14th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[2004 Indian general election|2004]]\n| 435\n| 19\n| 5.33\n| 6.66\n| Uttar Pradesh (19)\n|-\n| [[15th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[2009 Indian general election|2009]]\n| 500\n| 21\n| 6.17\n| 6.56\n| Madhya Pradesh(1)<br />Uttar Pradesh (20)\n|-\n| [[16th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[2014 Indian general election|2014]]\n| 503\n| 0\n| 4.19\n|\n| NA\n|-\n| [[17th Lok Sabha]]\n| [[2019 Indian general election|2019]]\n| 383\n| 10\n| 3.67\n|\n| Uttar Pradesh (10)\n|}\n\n=== Uttar Pradesh Legislative Assembly (Lower House) ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#00f;\"\n! Vidhan Sabha Term\n! UP <br />elections\n! Seats<br />contested\n! Seats<br />won\n! % of<br /> votes\n! % of votes in<br />seats contested\n|-\n| 12th Vidhan Sabha\n| 1993\n| 164\n| 67\n| 11.12\n| 28.52\n|-\n| 13th Vidhan Sabha\n| 1996\n| 296\n| 67\n| 19.64\n| 27.73\n|-\n| 14th Vidhan Sabha\n| [[2002 Uttar Pradesh Legislative Assembly election|2002]]\n| 401\n| 98\n| 23.06\n| 23.19\n|-\n| 15th Vidhan Sabha\n| [[2007 Uttar Pradesh state assembly elections|2007]]\n| 403\n| 206\n| 30.43\n| 30.43\n|-\n| 16th Vidhan Sabha\n| [[2012 Uttar Pradesh legislative assembly election|2012]]\n| 403\n| 80\n| 25.95\n| 25.95\n|-\n| 17th Vidhan Sabha\n| [[2017 Uttar Pradesh Legislative Assembly election|2017]]\n| 403\n| 19\n| 22.24\n| 22.24\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"text-alig