 Party Workers|website=News18|access-date=2019-01-03}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official}} \n{{Commons category|Bahujan Samaj Party}}\n\n{{Indian political parties}}\n\n[[Category:Bahujan Samaj Party|*]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1984]]\n[[Category:1984 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:National political parties in India]]\n[[Category:Ambedkarite political parties]]\n[[Category:Dalit politics]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the Nepalese party|Bahujan Samaj Party, Nepal}}\n\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox Indian Political Party\n |name            = Bahujan Samaj Party\n |logo            = [[File:Elephant Bahujan Samaj Party.svg|200px|Bahujan Samaj Party Flag]]\n |abbreviation    = BSP\n |colorcode       = {{Bahujan Samaj Party/meta/color}}\n |alliance        = \n |president       = [[Mayawati]]<ref>{{cite web |author=livemint |title=Mayawati says she will remain BSP president for next 20 years|website=livemint.com|url=https://www.livemint.com/Politics/PTjTr92SwEcPJ0ItjL4YuL/BSP-should-be-ready-to-fight-polls-solo-says-Mayawati.html|accessdate=2018-05-26}}</ref>\n |secretary       = \n* [[Satish Chandra Mishra]]\n* [[R S Kushwaha]]\n* [[Munquad Ali]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/bsp-munquad-ali-up-party-chief-danish-ali-shyam-singh-yadav-party-leader-lok-sabha-1578345-2019-08-07|title=BSP appoints Munquad Ali as UP party chief, Danish Ali removed as leader in LS|last=LucknowAugust 7|first=India Today Web Desk|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-08-08}}</ref>\n* Ram Achal Rajbhar\n* Mewalal Gautam<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/ex-bjp-leader-dayashankar-released-from-mau-jail/articleshow/53584371.cms |title=EX-BJP leader Dayashankar released from Mau jail|date=2016-08-07|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-04-27}}</ref>\n* [[R Sridhar]]<ref>{{cite n