{"title_page": "Sarah Jones (drummer)", "text_new": "{{short description|English drummer and singer}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| image          = Hot Chip Lollapalooza 2015-11.jpg\n| caption        = Jones drumming with [[Hot Chip]] at [[Lollapalooza]] 2015\n| name           = Sarah Jones\n| background     = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name     = \n| alias            = Pillow Person\n| birth_date     = 31 August 1985\n| birth_place    = [[London]], [[England]]\n| origin         = [[Hereford]], [[Herefordshire]], England\n| genre          = [[Alternative rock]], [[electronic music|electronic]], [[Pop music|pop]]\n| occupation     = Musician, drummer, songwriter, composer\n| years_active   = 2000\u2013present\n| instrument     = [[Drum kit|Drums]], [[synthesizer]], vocals\n| associated_acts= [[Harry Styles]], [[NYPC]], [[Hot Chip]], Pillow Person, [[NZCA_Lines|NZCA]], [[The Pussycat Dolls]]\n| website        = [https://pillowperson.bandcamp.com/ Pillow Person]\n}}\n'''Sarah Jones''' (born 31 August 1985) is an English musician based in [[London, England|London]], best known for her work as a session and touring drummer. She is a founding member of [[NYPC]], and has also served as a touring drummer for both English pop singer [[Harry Styles]], [[Bat for Lashes]]<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GPUdqvvs7qA</ref>, [[post-punk revival]] band [[Bloc Party]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/bloc-party-34-1255762|title=Bloc Party play last show before hiatus at Latitude Festival - NME|date=20 July 2013|work=NME|access-date=3 September 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> and [[synthpop]] band [[Hot Chip]]. Additionally, she has released several solo singles under the moniker of Pillow Person.\n\n== Early career==\nJones showed an interest in music from an early age. In an interview with ''Tom Tom Mag'', Jones stated that she \"started off playing the piano,\" and \"although [she] liked it,\" the piano \"wasn't exactly what [she] was looking for.\" Jones began learning the drums after a family friend left a kit at her house, being taught basic beats by her cousin. Jones also notes: \"My dad had some friends who would come around and play together on the weekends. I'd sit and watch them, and soon I started joining in.\" Soon, Jones began drumming in local bands and subsequently touring the UK and Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tomtommag.com/2013/07/hot-chips-hot-chip-sarah-jones/ |title=Hot Chip\u2019s Hot Chip: Sarah Jones |publisher=Tom Tom Mag}}</ref>\n\n==Harry Styles==\n[[File:Sarah-Jones-Drummer-Harry-Styles-Band-SAP-Center.png|thumb|Sarah Jones performing at the SAP Center with Harry Styles]]\n\nSarah Jones played drums and provided backing vocals for [[Harry Styles]]'s [[Harry Styles: Live on Tour|world tour]], including an April 2017 performance with Styles on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', playing \"Sign of the Times\" and \"Ever Since New York.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/erinchack/harry-styles-is-cool-an-all-but-lets-talk-about-his-drummer |title=Harry Styles Is Cool And All But Let's Talk About His Drummer Sarah Jones\n|publisher=BuzzFeed}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bandwagon.asia/articles/a-guide-to-harry-styles-band-and-no-we-don-t-mean-one-direction |title=A guide to Harry Styles\u2019 band, and no, we don\u2019t mean One Direction\n|publisher=Bandwagon}}</ref> The tour itself began on September 19 2017, and ended on July 14 2018.\n\nJones has continued as drummer for Styles following his sophomore record 'Fine Line' (2019), including its promotion and upcoming world tour \"Love on Tour\" (2020) <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Tqm7-zN5s8k</ref>.\n\n==Pillow Person==\nSarah Jones has written and performed three [[electropop]] songs (\"Go Ahead (2016)\", \"On Your Way (2017)\", \"Kitchen (2017)\") under the name Pillow Person.,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.loudandquiet.com/interview/somehow-sarah-jones-managed-find-time-create-pillow-person/ |title=Somehow Sarah Jones has managed to find time to create Pillow Person\n |publisher=Loud and Quiet}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nylon.com/articles/sarah-jones-harry-styles-drummer-kitchen-video |title=Sarah Jones Is Harry Styles\u2019 Drummer\u2014She\u2019s Also A Half-Fake Pillow Person\n |publisher=NYLON}}</ref>\n\n==NYPC==\n[[File:Sarah-Jones-Drummer-NYPC-Neck-Of-The-Woods.png|thumb|Sarah Jones performing with NYPC, Neck of the Woods, San Francisco]]\n\nSarah Jones is a member of [[NYPC]] (originally New Young Pony Club), an [[electronic music]] band which released three albums between 2007-2013.\n\n==The Pussycat Dolls==\nSarah Jones played drums as a member of [[The Pussycat Dolls]] band tour ''[[Unfinished Business (tour)|Unfinished Business]]'' (2020).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://pillowperson.bandcamp.com/ Pillow Person (Bandcamp)]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jones, Sarah}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hereford]]\n[[Category:English rock drummers]]\n[[Category:21st-century drummers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English drummer and singer}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| image          = Hot Chip Lollapalooza 2015-11.jpg\n| caption        = Jones drumming with [[Hot Chip]] at [[Lollapalooza]] 2015\n| name           = Sarah Jones\n| background     = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name     = \n| alias            = Pillow Person\n| birth_date     = 31 August 1985\n| birth_place    = [[London]], [[England]]\n| origin         = [[Hereford]], [[Herefordshire]], England\n| genre          = [[Alternative rock]], [[electronic music|electronic]], [[Pop music|pop]]\n| occupation     = Musician, drummer, songwriter, composer\n| years_active   = 2000\u2013present\n| instrument     = [[Drum kit|Drums]], [[synthesizer]], vocals\n| associated_acts= [[Harry Styles]], [[NYPC]], [[Hot Chip]], Pillow Person, [[NZCA_Lines|NZCA]], [[The Pussycat Dolls]]\n| website        = [https://pillowperson.bandcamp.com/ Pillow Person]\n}}\n'''Sarah Jones''' (born 31 August 1985) is an English musician based in [[London, England|London]], best known for her work as a session and touring drummer. She is a founding member of [[NYPC]], and has also served as a touring drummer for both English pop singer [[Harry Styles]], [[Bat for Lashes]]<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GPUdqvvs7qA</ref>, [[post-punk revival]] band [[Bloc Party]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/bloc-party-34-1255762|title=Bloc Party play last show before hiatus at Latitude Festival - NME|date=20 July 2013|work=NME|access-date=3 September 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> and [[synthpop]] band [[Hot Chip]]. Additionally, she has released several solo singles under the moniker of Pillow Person.\n\n== Early career==\nJones showed an interest in music from an early age. In an interview with ''Tom Tom Mag'', Jones stated that she \"started off playing the piano,\" and \"although [she] liked it,\" the piano \"wasn't exactly what [she] was looking for.\" Jones began learning the drums after a family friend left a kit at her house, being taught basic beats by her cousin. Jones also notes: \"My dad had some friends who would come around and play together on the weekends. I'd sit and watch them, and soon I started joining in.\" Soon, Jones began drumming in local bands and subsequently touring the UK and Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tomtommag.com/2013/07/hot-chips-hot-chip-sarah-jones/ |title=Hot Chip\u2019s Hot Chip: Sarah Jones |publisher=Tom Tom Mag}}</ref>\n\n==Harry Styles==\n[[File:Sarah-Jones-Drummer-Harry-Styles-Band-SAP-Center.png|thumb|Sarah Jones performing at the SAP Center with Harry Styles]]\n\nSarah Jones played drums and provided backing vocals for [[Harry Styles]]'s [[Harry Styles: Live on Tour|world tour]], including an April 2017 performance with Styles on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', playing \"Sign of the Times\" and \"Ever Since New York.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/erinchack/harry-styles-is-cool-an-all-but-lets-talk-about-his-drummer |title=Harry Styles Is Cool And All But Let's Talk About His Drummer Sarah Jones\n|publisher=BuzzFeed}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bandwagon.asia/articles/a-guide-to-harry-styles-band-and-no-we-don-t-mean-one-direction |title=A guide to Harry Styles\u2019 band, and no, we don\u2019t mean One Direction\n|publisher=Bandwagon}}</ref> The tour itself began on September 19 2017, and ended on July 14 2018.\n\nJones has continued as drummer for Styles following his sophomore record 'Fine Line' (2019), including its promotion and upcoming world tour \"Love on Tour\" (2020) <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Tqm7-zN5s8k</ref>.\n\n==Pillow Person==\nSarah Jones has written and performed three [[electropop]] songs (\"Go Ahead (2016)\", \"On Your Way (2017)\", \"Kitchen (2017)\") under the name Pillow Person.,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.loudandquiet.com/interview/somehow-sarah-jones-managed-find-time-create-pillow-person/ |title=Somehow Sarah Jones has managed to find time to create Pillow Person\n |publisher=Loud and Quiet}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nylon.com/articles/sarah-jones-harry-styles-drummer-kitchen-video |title=Sarah Jones Is Harry Styles\u2019 Drummer\u2014She\u2019s Also A Half-Fake Pillow Person\n |publisher=NYLON}}</ref>\n\n==NYPC==\n[[File:Sarah-Jones-Drummer-NYPC-Neck-Of-The-Woods.png|thumb|Sarah Jones performing with NYPC, Neck of the Woods, San Francisco]]\n\nSarah Jones is a member of [[NYPC]] (originally New Young Pony Club), an [[electronic music]] band which released three albums between 2007-2013.\n\n==The Pussycat Dolls==\nSarah Jones played drums a members of [[The Pussycat Dolls]] band tour ''[[Unfinished Business (tour)|Unfinished Business]]'' (2020).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://pillowperson.bandcamp.com/ Pillow Person (Bandcamp)]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jones, Sarah}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hereford]]\n[[Category:English rock drummers]]\n[[Category:21st-century drummers]]\n", "name_user": "DublinRanch", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eThe Pussycat Dolls:typo fix", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarah_Jones_(drummer)"}
